@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix tgs: <http://example.org/tgs#> .
@prefix thinkr: <http://example.org/thinkr#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

<http://example.org/tgs#> a owl:Ontology ;
    owl:imports <http://example.org/thinkr#> ;
    rdfs:comment "Imports tgs-core for Protege compatibility — editing this file alone will resolve thinkr: classes/properties via the catalog file."@en .

#############################################
# SCRATCH FILE — established 2026-07-14, after the second real
# instance of the same mistake (Concept-lineage facts landing in
# linknotes.ttl instead of concepts.ttl, mid-Batch-5-migration; before
# that, similar mid-task drift into whatever file happened to be open).
# See docs/sidecar-cleanup-handoff.md for the full incident and the
# discussion that led to this file.
#
# THE RULE THIS FILE EXISTS TO PROTECT: every other file in data/seed/
# holds instances of exactly ONE class (its own titular class) and
# nothing else — enforced by scripts/validate_class_purity.py. That
# rule is easy to break mid-task: a new fact naturally wants to go
# wherever the current work is already centered, not necessarily its
# own actual home file. This file is the legitimate place for that
# impulse to go instead, so mid-task flow doesn't require a context
# switch to the "correct" file before the surrounding work is even
# finished.
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
# 1. Add a partial/provisional statement here, with an explicit
#    destination comment directly above it — e.g.:
#      # destined for: concepts.ttl (Concept.EnergyBlindness's own block)
#      tgs:Concept.EnergyBlindness thinkr:influencedBy tgs:Persona.ArtBerman .
# 2. This file IS loaded by scripts/load_oxigraph.sh like every other
#    seed file — scratch content is queryable and testable while it's
#    still here, not invisible until promoted.
# 3. Before considering ANY batch/task done: sweep every statement here
#    into its real destination file (merged into the subject's own
#    existing individual block, not left as an orphaned triple — see
#    concepts.ttl for the pattern), then delete it from this file.
# 4. A task is NOT complete while this file has content in it. Run
#    scripts/validate_class_purity.py --check-scratch-empty as part of
#    the same "verify before declaring done" pass every other batch in
#    this project already requires.
#
# WHAT NEVER BELONGS HERE: schema (classes/properties — those go in
# tgs-core.ttl or enumerations.ttl directly, they're not "partial"),
# anything you're confident is a permanent, complete fact (just write
# it to its real file directly), or anything you intend to leave
# unswept across sessions (if it needs to survive a session boundary
# incomplete, it belongs in docs/sidecar-cleanup-handoff.md as a
# tracked open item instead, not silently parked here).
#############################################

# (currently empty — nothing in flight)
